reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 4, 2024
reviews.reviewText: I love these lamps! They are the perfect size for a nightstand. The 3 levels of brightness using touch is a wonderful feature! Easy to assemble and great quality for the price! Would definitely buy again if needed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 5, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Got this lamp for my son’s room. It’s very modern and simple looking, which is what I wanted. It’s also easy to turn on and off with just tapping on the lamp base instead of pressing a button on the wire. It came with a lightbulb with a nice warm light. I really like this lamp. Makes the room feel very cozy.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Pretty functional and good looking for the price
reviews.reviewText: This is my first touch lamp. I like the 3 levels of brightness. Easy of course to turn on and off in the dark without fumbling for a switch. Looks pretty good. I'd say it's good quality for the money but not impressive.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 5, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I was a litttttle worried before they arrived that the gold would be too much of a shinny gold,( if you know what I mean), but they’re absolutely beautiful!! I love that it’s touch sensitive and has 3 diff levels of brightness! I love that it can charge my phone, too! These lamps complete the look of my bedroom and I’m beyond satisfied with this purchase!! They’re very easy to assemble, as well!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Stylish and works great
reviews.reviewText: My wife chose it and I just bought it on my account. This pair is beautiful and the golden color of the base combines very well with any light or dark furniture, giving the impression of luxury. The first touch turns on a weaker light, on the second touch it turns on medium light and on the third touch it turns on a higher light. On the fourth touch on the base, it turns off. I used my USB tester and tested the two USB outputs that are correctly supplying 4.97 Volts (up to 5.05 is acceptable) and 0.28-0.35 Ampere when charging a cell phone or any device of the same size (like most USBs). The entire base is a sensor and any touch turns on the lamp. There could be a small "neutral" circular area (at the bottom of the base, for example) that would allow it to be dragged to the side for cleaning without accidentally turning it on and having to press 3 more times to turn the lamp off. But as it is, it's quite pleasing and this isn't a major inconvenience. The quality of the dome is very good (not excellent) and the retro-style multifilament bulb is very cool, without getting too hot. I've been using it for 1 week.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Beautiful and functional
reviews.reviewText: Love how the lamp looks on our dresser. 3 brightness level and 2 usb ports. Very good value for the price!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 3, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Gorgeous Base, Cheap Shade
reviews.reviewText: I have a major thing for any kind of celestial/witchy print, so as soon as I saw this lamp I knew I had to have it for my bedside table and it doesn't disappoint!The base of the lamp is incredibly high quality. The brassy color is gorgeous and elegant and looks really beautiful against the contrast of the light shade. The 'touch' to turn on feature is also really cool- the lamp turns on for three different brightness levels; first touch is dim (like a night light) second touch is medium bright, and the third touch is the brightest level. All the USB port work well, and the lamp really does look charming when it's turned on and the shapes are projected onto the wall.Two major complaints though: the lamp shade looks and feels disappointingly cheap. It's pretty much just paper on two metal rings. It looks flimsy, and it when the light isn't on the lack of quality is apparent. I love the design, I just wish it was a bit thicker. Also, the lamp seems to flicker frequently when it's turned on as though the base is overly sensitive to touch. It's not the lightbulb or the outlet (I've checked). Even if there's nothing and no one near the lamp, it goes in and out after an hour or so. Just something to keep in mind.All in all, I am happy with this lamp. It's really pretty and I wanted it mostly for looks so I don't mind the flaws too much but it is something to keep in mind.
